    • Method Detail

      • unmodifiableKeyStore

        public static KeyStore unmodifiableKeyStore​(KeyStore toWrap)
                                     throws NoSuchAlgorithmException,
                                            CertificateException,
                                            IOException
        Wrap an existing initialised KeyStore with an unmodifiable wrapper. Note: References are held to the underlying KeyStore can still be modified and changes will still be visible in the representation returned here.
        Parameters:
        toWrap - the KeyStore to wrap.
        Returns:
        the unmodifiable wrapper around the KeyStore
        Throws:
        NoSuchAlgorithmException
        CertificateException
        IOException
        IllegalArgumentException - if the KeyStore being wrapped is null
